entry.def: A rabbi is a Jewish religious leader, usually one who is in charge of a synagogue, one who is qualified to teach Judaism, or one who is an expert on Jewish law.

means.word_mean: 1. spiritual leader of a Jewish congregation; qualified to expound and apply Jewish law
